 <br>
<h3 class="text-light">Geological Disasters</h3> 
<ul class="text-light">
    These originate from movements or changes within the Earth.
    <li>Earthquakes – Sudden shaking of the ground due to tectonic activity.</li>
<li> Volcanic Eruptions – Explosive release of lava, ash, and gases from volcanoes.</li>
<li>Landslides – Rapid movement of rock, earth, or debris down a slope.</li>
<li>Avalanches – Sudden downhill flow of snow and ice, often in mountainous regions.</li>
</ul>

